verbs.description: prolificate (third-person singular simple present prolificates, present participle prolificating, simple past and past participle prolificated)

entries.meaning: (dated, transitive) To make prolific; to fertilize; to impregnate.
examples: ...it enables simultaneous and self-consistent treatment of the magnetic circuit together with the associated purely electrical circuits and should prolificate the understanding and usage of electromagnetic components and systems.
